--[[
	BuildClient v9 Pastel + Performance (LocalScript)
	LOCATION: StarterGui - paste over the previous version

	New in v9:
	  - FIX: bare D no longer copies (it is the strafe key!). Walking right
	    with a wall/floor selected was silently cloning it in place - that
	    was the "duplicates every 3-5 seconds" bug. Copy is now Ctrl+D.
	  - FIX: GUI hiding is tag-based. Startup recovery only re-enables
	    interfaces THIS script hid, so other systems' intentionally
	    disabled GUIs (second inventory panel!) stay asleep.
	  - Kid-friendly pastel light theme matching the plot picker.
	  - Zero idle polling: the canbuild server poll is now a client-side
	    check scheduled only while the dock is open; the watchdog loop is
	    gone; free-cam's render loop exists only while flying; the time
	    preview is driven by a ClockTime listener instead of a loop.
	  - Hover raycasts are skipped entirely on touch devices.
	  - Quick-action tinting only writes when the state actually changes.

	Kept from v8.x: kid-friendly Select controls, story indices, Stack Up,
	Floor Focus / Hide Roofs cutaway, window sill controls, roof grid/
	overhang/rotation, wall corner auto-snap, server-validated permissions.
]]

